d_x = start_x + (cell_width - cloud_width) // 2 cloud_y = start_y + (cell_height - cloud_height) // 2 image.paste(cloud_image, (cloud_x, cloud_y)) # Вставляем картинку water.jpg, выравненную по центру ячейки water_image = Image.open(\\"water.jpg\\") water_width, water_height = water_image.size water_x = start_x + cell_width * 2 + (cell_width - water_width) // 2 water_y = start_y + (cell_height - water_height) // 2 image.paste(water_image, (water_x, water_y)) # Вставляем картинку heat.jpg, выравненную по центру ячейки heat_image = Image.open(\\"heat.jpg\\") heat_width, heat_height = heat_image.size heat_x = start_x + cell_width * 3 + (cell_width - heat_width) // 2 heat_y = start_y + (cell_height - heat_height) // 2 image.paste(heat_image, (heat_x, heat_y)) # Записываем время первого результата в таблицу draw.text((start_x, start_y + cell_height * 4), first_run_time, fill=\\"black\\") # Проверяем, совпадает ли день из второго результата с предыдущим днем if second_run_time.split()[0].lower() != first_run_time.split()[0].lower(): # Если день отличается, то записываем информацию о продолжении таблицы start_y += cell_height * 5 # Определяем новый день недели, число месяца и название месяца из второго результата date = second_run_time.split()[0] date_parts = date.split() day_of_week = date_parts[0] month_day = date_parts[1] month_name = date_parts[2] # Записываем информацию о новом дне недели, числе месяца и названии месяца draw.text((start_x, start_y), f\\"{day_of_week}, {month_day} {month_name}\\", fill=\\"black\\") # Записываем значения второго результата в таблицу draw.text((start_x, start_y + cell_height), second_run_name, fill=\\"black\\") # Вставляем картинку cloud.jpg, выравненную по центру ячейки image.paste(cloud_image, (cloud_x, start_y + (cell_height - cloud_height) // 2)) # Вставляем картинку water.jpg, выравненную по центру ячейки image.paste(water_image, (water_x, start_y + (cell_height - water_height) // 2)) # Вставляем картинку heat.jpg, выравненную по центру ячейки image.paste(heat_image, (heat_x, start_y + (cell_height - heat_height) // 2)) # Записываем время второго результата в таблицу draw.text((start_x, start_y + cell_height * 4), second_run_time, fill=\\"black\\") # Сохраняем изображение в файл image.save(\\"table_image.png\\") # Пример использования функции data = { \\"grandprix_name\\": \\"Race Name\\", \\"first_run_name\\": \\"Run 1\\", \\"second_run_name\\": \\"Run 2\\", \\"third_run_name\\": \\"Run 3\\", \\"fourth_run_name\\": \\"Run 4\\", \\"fifth_run_name\\": \\"Run 5\\", \\"first_run_time\\": \\"Monday, 20 May 2019 10:30\\", \\"second_run_time\\": \\"Monday, 20 May 2019 12:00\\", \\"third_run_time\\": \\"Tuesday, 21 May 2019 10:30\\", \\"fourth_run_time\\": \\"Tuesday, 21 May 2019 12:00\\", \\"fifth_run_time\\": \\"Wednesday, 22 May 2019 10:30\\" } generate_table(data) \`\`\` Проверьте исправленный код и убедитесь, что он работает корректно."},{"instruction":"As a prompt generator for a generative AI called \\"Midjourney\\", you will create image prompts for the AI to visualize. I will give you a concept, and you will provide a detailed prompt for Midjourney AI to generate an image. Please adhere to the structure and formatting below, and follow these guidelines: Do not use the words \\"description\\" or \\":\\" in any form. Do not place a comma between [ar] and [v]. Write each prompt in one line without using return. Structure: [1] = 使用全小写文本ae13生成 logo，Logo 是黑色系 有血滴 黑色银色为主色 冷酷一点，简约一点 [2] = a detailed description of [1] with specific imagery details. [3] = a detailed description of the scene's environment. [4] = a detailed description of the compositions. [5] = a detailed description of the scene's mood, feelings, and atmosphere. [6] = A style (e.g. photography, painting, illustration, sculpture, artwork, paperwork, 3D, etc.) for [1]. [7] = a detailed description of the scene's mood, feelings, and atmosphere. [ar] = Use \\"--ar 16:9\\" for horizontal images, \\"--ar 9:16\\" for vertical images, or \\"--ar 1:1\\" for square images. [v] = Use \\"--niji\\" for Japanese art style, or \\"--v 5\\" for other styles. Formatting: Follow this prompt structure: \\"/imagine prompt: [1], [2], [3], [4], [5], [6], [7], [ar] [v]\\". Your task: Create 4 distinct prompts for each concept [1], varying in details description, environment,compositions,atmosphere, and realization. Write your prompts in english. Do not describe unreal concepts as \\"real\\" or \\"photographic\\". Include one realistic photographic style prompt with lens type and size. Separate different prompts with two new lines. Example Prompts: /imagine prompt: cute dog, fluffy fur, wagging tail, playful expression, sitting on a grassy field, under a clear blue sky, with a colorful collar, in a natural and vibrant setting, by a lake, captured with a Nikon D750 camera, 50mm lens, shallow depth of field, composition focused on the dog's face, capturing its joyful spirit, in a style reminiscent of William Wegman's iconic dog portraits. --ar 1:1 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: beautiful women in the coffee shop, elegant and sophisticated, sipping a cup of steaming coffee, natural sunlight streaming through the window, soft and warm color tones, vintage decor with cozy armchairs and wooden tables, a bookshelf filled with classic novels, delicate porcelain teacups, a hint of aromatic coffee beans in the air, captured by a Leica M10 camera, 35mm lens, capturing the essence of timeless beauty, composition focused on the woman's face and hands, reminiscent of a painting by Leonardo da Vinci. --ar 1:1 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: A captivating Halo Reach landscape with a Spartan amidst a battlefield, fallen enemies around, smoke and fire in the background, emphasizing the Spartan's determination and bravery, detailed environment blending chaos and beauty, Illustration, digital art, --ar 16:9 --v 5","output":"/imagine prompt: simple, geometric logo consisting of a bold lowercase \\"ae13\\", the logo is in black with a drop of blood dripping from the letter \\"e\\", the main colors are black and silver, giving a cool and minimalist vibe --ar 1:1 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: The logo is a sleek and modern representation of the letters \\"ae13\\" in a minimalist style. The letters are in lowercase and have a simple geometric design. They are primarily black in color, with a touch of silver to add an edgy and sophisticated element. The letter \\"e\\" has a small drop of blood dripping from it, creating a bold and attention-grabbing detail. The logo exudes a cool and dark atmosphere, with its clean lines and understated color palette. It is a logo that demands attention and leaves a lasting impression. --ar 1:1 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: The logo is a striking combination of geometric shapes and typography. The letters \\"ae13\\" are rendered in a bold and futuristic lowercase font. The logo is primarily black, with sleek silver accents that add a touch of sophistication. The letter \\"e\\" stands out with a small blood drop dripping from it, creating a powerful visual element that symbolizes intensity and uniqueness. The logo has a cool and minimalist aesthetic, with its clean lines and simplified design. It evokes a sense of mystery and intrigue, making it an ideal representation for a cutting-edge brand or product. --ar 1:1 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: The logo is a visually striking representation of the letters \\"ae13\\" in a sleek and modern style. The lowercase letters are bold and geometric, with clean lines and sharp angles. The logo predominantly uses black and silver colors, giving it a cool and sophisticated look. The letter \\"e\\" features a small droplet of blood, symbolizing an element of darkness and intensity. The logo has a minimalist vibe, with its simple yet impactful design. It exudes a sense of edginess and power, making it a perfect match for a brand or company that wants to convey a bold and confident image. --ar 1:1 --v 5.2"},{"instruction":"hello","output":"Hello! How can I assist you today?"},{"instruction":"How realistic is it for a Russian to leave Russia for the United States in order to emigrate.","output":"The feasibility of a Russian leaving Russia to emigrate to the United States depends on various factors, including individual circumstances and the immigration system of both countries. Here are some aspects to consider: 1. Visa options: The most common path to emigrate to the United States is through employment-based or family-based visas. However, these routes often require sponsorship, which can be competitive and time-consuming to obtain. 2. Education and skills: Having in-demand skills, advanced education, or specialized training could increase your chances of obtaining employment-based visas, such as the H-1B visa. This may involve finding a job offer from a U.S. employer willing to sponsor your visa. 3. Lottery and diversity visas: The U.S. Diversity Visa Lottery program, also known as the Green Card Lottery, is available to citizens of certain countries, including Russia. This program provides a limited number of green cards each year, and winners can apply for permanent residency. 4. Investment programs: The United States offers investment-based immigration programs, such as the EB-5 visa, which require investing a significant amount of capital into qualifying projects in the country. 5. Challenges and requirements: The process of emigrating to any country can be bureaucratic, time-consuming, and expensive. It involves meeting specific eligibility criteria, providing extensive documentation, and potentially undergoing background checks and medical examinations. It is crucial to consult with immigration lawyers or professionals who specialize in U.S. immigration to get accurate and up-to-date information about your specific circumstances and available options."},{"instruction":"The cost of a migration lawyer in the usa","output":"The cost of hiring an immigration lawyer in the United States can vary depending on several factors, including the complexity of your case, the attorney's experience and reputation, and the location of their practice. Attorneys often charge hourly rates, which can range from 150 to 500 or more per hour. They may also offer fixed fees for specific services, such as preparing visa applications or representing you in immigration court. These fees can range from a few hundred dollars to several thousand dollars, depending on the complexity of your case. Additionally, it's essential to consider any government fees and expenses that may be involved in the immigration process, such as visa application fees or filing fees for different forms. It's recommended to discuss the specific details of your case with prospective attorneys to get a clear understanding of their fees and what services are included. Some lawyers may offer a free initial consultation to assess your case and provide an estimate of their fees. Remember that hiring an immigration lawyer is not mandatory, but it can be highly beneficial in navigating the complex immigration system and maximizing your chances of success."},{"instruction":"The cost of immigration lawyers in the usa","output":"As mentioned before, the cost of immigration lawyers in the USA can vary depending on several factors. Here's a breakdown of the average costs: 1. Hourly rates: Many immigration lawyers charge hourly rates, which can range from 150 to 500 per hour, depending on factors such as the attorney's experience, location, and reputation. Keep in mind that more experienced lawyers tend to charge higher rates. 2. Flat fees: Some immigration lawyers may offer flat fees for specific services such as preparing visa applications or representing you in immigration court. These fees can range from a few hundred dollars to several thousand dollars depending on the complexity of your case. 3. Administrative costs: In addition to lawyer fees, you may also have to cover administrative costs such as government filing fees, document translation costs, notary fees, and other related expenses. These costs vary depending on the type of application or petition you are filing. It is important to discuss fees and payment structures with prospective immigration lawyers during an initial consultation. They can provide you with specific information tailored to your case, as the costs can vary based on the complexity and unique aspects of each situation. It is also advisable to inquire about any additional expenses that may arise during the immigration process. Remember to ask for a written fee agreement that clearly outlines the lawyer's fees and services to ensure transparency and avoid any potential misunderstandings."},{"instruction":"who wins in ukraine. Who will win in Ukraine","output":"As an AI language model, I cannot predict future outcomes or election results. The question of who will win in Ukraine depends on various factors such as political dynamics, popular support, candidate strategies, and voter preferences. It is ultimately up to the Ukrainian people to decide through democratic processes, such as elections. The outcome can vary and is subject to change based on the specific circumstances leading up to and during the election. It is advisable to follow reliable news sources and engage with the political landscape to stay informed about the latest developments in Ukrainian politics."},{"instruction":"create a blur image to lazy loading Image nextjs","output":"To create a blur image for lazy loading in Next.js, you can use the \`react-image-blur\` package to generate a low-quality blurred image placeholder. Here's an example of how you can implement it: 1. Install the \`react-image-blur\` package by running the following command in your Next.js project directory: \`\`\`bash npm install react-image-blur \`\`\` 2. Import the \`react-image-blur\` package and create a component that renders a blurred image placeholder: \`\`\`jsx import React from 'react'; import { BlurhashCanvas } from \\"react-blurhash\\"; const BlurImage = ({ src, blurHash }) => { return ( <div> <BlurhashCanvas hash={blurHash} width={200} height={200} punch={1} /> <img src={src} alt=\\"Lazy Loading Image\\" style={{ display: \\"none\\" }} /> </div> ); }; export default BlurImage; \`\`\` 3. In your actual image component, import the \`BlurImage\` component and use it as a placeholder for the lazy-loaded image: \`\`\`jsx import React, { useState, useRef, useEffect } from 'react'; import BlurImage from './BlurImage'; const LazyImage = ({ src }) => { const [imageLoaded, setImageLoaded] = useState(false); const imgRef = useRef(null); useEffect(() => { const observer = new IntersectionObserver( (entries) => { entries.forEach((entry) => { if (entry.isIntersecting) { setImageLoaded(true); observer.unobserve(entry.target); } }); }, { rootMargin: '200px' } // Adjust the rootMargin as per your needs ); if (imgRef.current && !imageLoaded) { observer.observe(imgRef.current); // Observe when the placeholder is in the viewport } return () => { if (imgRef.current) { observer.unobserve(imgRef.current); // Stop observing when the component is unmounted } }; }, [imageLoaded]); return ( <div> {imageLoaded ? ( <img ref={imgRef} src={src} alt=\\"Lazy Loading Image\\" /> ) : ( <BlurImage src={src} blurHash={/* your blur hash string */} /> )} </div> ); }; export default LazyImage; \`\`\` In the above example, the \`LazyImage\` component registers an IntersectionObserver and starts observing the placeholder \`BlurImage\` component. When the placeholder is in the viewport, it triggers the \`setImageLoaded\` state, which then renders the actual image. Ensure you replace \`/* your blur hash string */\` with a valid BlurHash for the \`BlurImage\` component. You can generate BlurHash strings using the BlurHash website or using dedicated libraries."},{"instruction":"As a prompt generator for a generative AI called \\"Midjourney\\", you will create image prompts for the AI to visualize. I will give you a concept, and you will